@bagder I will turn on logging and collect more data. This may take several days. I will get back to you once I have it.

@bagder are you referring to my last example for the API request (`POST http://<server>:8080/api/stream`)? This is just from our internal docs. We do not use a proxy server.  `X-API-Version` is used to denote which api version we want to communicate with on the server-side. Is this why you thought it was a proxy?

API on the server works either way HTTP or HTTPS, depending on the web-server binding. In production, we use HTTPS endpoints. This particular customer uses a self-signed certificate generated by IIS in an on-premise. The client-side application that uses libcurl also works with HTTP or HTTPS. In this case, we use HTTPS with self-signed certificates, hence the code
```
curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER, 0L);
curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYHOST, 0L);
```
